Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Slice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ¼-inch-thick rounds. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, peel and dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced). Halve @potato buns{2}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon}, @ketchup{2%tablespoon}, @ancho chili powder{1%teaspoon}, @Beef Stock Concentrate{1}, half the @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, and 1 TBSP water. Set aside.

> For 4 servings, use all the cornstarch and 2 TBSP water.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @ground beef{10%ounce}; season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{3-5%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Add BBQ sauce mixture to pan with beef. Cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened and beef is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

While filling cooks, toast buns in a #toaster{} until golden brown.

Fill buns with as much beef filling and @sliced dill pickle{1%unit} as you like. Divide sloppy joes between plates. Serve with potatoes and any remaining pickle on the side.